George Bizos will be honoured with a Special Official Funeral Category One. JOHANNESBURG - Human rights lawyer George Bizos will be laid to rest on Thursday. He died at his home last week at the age of 92. READ:Â Flags will fly at half-mast to honour George Bizos Many have praised Bizos for his dedication in the fight for human rights, with President Cyril Ramaphosa hailing him as one of the architects of our Constitution. He'll be honoured with a Special Official Funeral Category One.